{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"44ce5d0f217cfe25206a2dc44a18a9a4fcab26c6"},"timestamp":1581431470,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU1NjMyNDU4MjY=","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/104","origin":"github"},"title":"seahash() implementation will not produce correct results","message":"During block operation while loop will do 'len -= 32' which means on the [line 119](https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/blob/2cbc8cbf0d98054f6d57d29300bd5337402358d8/seahash.c#L119) len will not have its original value for anything bigger than 32 bytes, so 'a ^= len' in the final state will produce incorrect result.\n\nFrom the reference:\n\"Let the final state be (x, y, z, w). Then the final result is given by H = g(x ⊕ y ⊕ z ⊕ w ⊕ l) where l is the number of bytes in the original buffer.\"","files":null}]}